      {
        "id": 3855152,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-07-25T20:43:27.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"9\" data-topic=\"174809\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Anyone try the '18 yet?  It just hit my market\u2026 must-buy in every vintage for me but haven\u2019t seen a note in WA or elsewhere yet.  Thanks.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>That will be coming out in my M\u00e2connais report next month, but it\u2019s ample, satiny and honeyed, with quite a giving profile but also impressive freshness. You might think of it as a more sun-kissed version of the 2012 for example, even though the two years have almost nothing in common on paper.</p>\n<p>The patient will want to buy some 2017 Levrout\u00e9e when that comes out at the end of the year.</p>",
